title: Back To Black
notes:
This is the original US pressing with small "Parental Advisory Explicit Content" emblem at bottom right of front cover. The repress [r=1020679] came out a year later, which is discernible from this edition as the repress has a larger "Parental Advisory" logo on the bottom left-hand corner of the front cover.

Mastering/runout variant to otherwise identical [r=8236333], with lacquer cut at [l=Sterling Sound] for the East Coast market, instead of [l=The Mastering Lab] (TML) for the West Coast market.

℗ & © 2006 Island Records (UK) licensed exclusively to Universal Records, a Division of UMG Recordings, Inc.

All tracks published by EMI Music Publishing, except A5 published by EMI Blackwood Music Inc., EMI Music Publ. Ltd., Inouye Music (BMI), track B7 published by EMI Music Publishing, Jobete Music Inc, Jobete Music (UK) Ltd. and track B4 published by EMI Music Publishing, IQ Music Ltd.

Tracks A1, A2, A5, A6, B8 and B10: Mixed for osOHso.
Tracks A3, A4 and B9: Recorded at Instrument Zoo, Miami, Fl. Mixed at Circle House Studios, Miami, Fl.
Track B7: Recorded at Instrument Zoo, Miami, Fl. Mixed for osOHso.
Tracks A1, A2, A5, A6, B8, B11: Recorded at Dapking Studios, Chung King Studios and Metropolis Studios, London.
Track B10: Recorded at Daptone Studios, Allido Studios and Metropolis Studios.

Track B7: Contains a sample interpolation of "Ain't No Mountain High Enough" published by Jobete Music Inc and Jobete Music (UK) Ltd.
Track B10: Contains a sample interpolation of "She's A Fox Now" published by IQ Music Ltd.
Track B11: Ghostface Killah appears courtesy of Def Jam Records.

Tracks sequentially numbered on back cover. Durations not printed on release.

Runouts are etched, except "STERLING," which is stamped.
